In this compound, we have one oxygen atom (from the methoxy group), one nitrogen atom (from the piperidine ring), one carbon atom (from the methyl group attached to the piperidine ring), one carbon atom (from the methoxy group), three carbon atoms (from the propan-2-ol group), and eight hydrogen atoms (from the methyl and methoxy groups).

Based on this information, we can construct the molecular formula of the compound as C10H21NO3.
